Document: PhysicsShapeQueryParameters3D
Path: godot/classes/class_physicsshapequeryparameters3d.rst
Summary: Defines parameters for physics shape queries in 3D.

Inherits: Object

This class holds parameters for shape queries in 3D physics. It's used by methods like PhysicsDirectSpaceState3D.shape_collide and PhysicsDirectSpaceState3D.intersect_shape.

Properties:
shape_rid (RID): The RID of the shape resource to use for the query.
shape_form (Variant): The transform of the shape relative to the query origin.
motion (Vector3): The motion vector to check for collisions.
margin (float): The margin to use for the shape query.
collision_mask (int): The collision layers to check against.
exclude (Array[RID]): An array of RIDs to exclude from the query.
collide_with_bodies (bool): Whether to collide with physics bodies.
collide_with_areas (bool): Whether to collide with physics areas.
space_override (PhysicsServer3D.SpaceOverrideMode): The space override mode to use.
space_override_தரவு (Variant): The data for the space override.
one_way_collision_down_direction (Vector3): The direction for one-way collisions.
one_way_collision_max_depth (float): The maximum depth for one-way collisions.
trip_on_contact (bool): Whether to trip on contact.
query_rid (RID): The RID of the query.
owner_rid (RID): The RID of the owner.
