Document: PhysicsShapeQueryParameters3d
Path: godot/classes/class_physicsshapequeryparameters3d.rst
Summary: Configures parameters for PhysicsDirectSpaceState3D query methods.
By changing various properties of this object, such as the shape, you can configure the parameters for PhysicsDirectSpaceState3D's methods.
---CHUNK---
Document: PhysicsShapeQueryParameters3D
Path: godot/classes/class_physicsshapequeryparameters3d.rst
Summary: Defines the properties for configuring a physics shape query in 3D.

Properties:
- collide_with_areas (bool): If true, the query will detect collisions with Area3D objects. Default: false.
- collide_with_bodies (bool): If true, the query will detect collisions with PhysicsBody3D objects. Default: true.
- collision_mask (int): The collision layers to check against. Default: 4294967295.
- exclude (Array[RID]): An array of RIDs to exclude from the query. Default: [].
- margin (float): The margin to use for the shape query. Default: 0.0.
- motion (Vector3): The motion vector to consider for the query. Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0).
- shape (Resource): The shape resource to use for the query.
- shape_rid (RID): The RID of the shape to use for the query. Default: RID().
- transform (Transform3D): The transform of the shape to use for the query. Default: Transform3D(1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0).
---CHUNK---
Document: PhysicsShapeQueryParameters3D
Path: godot/classes/class_physicsshapequeryparameters3d.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of PhysicsShapeQueryParameters3D, which are used to configure physics queries in Godot.

Property Descriptions
Property: collide_with_areas
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If true, the query will take Area3D s into account.
Setget: set_collide_with_areas, is_collide_with_areas_enabled

Property: collide_with_bodies
Type: bool
Default: true
Description: If true, the query will take PhysicsBody3D s into account.
Setget: set_collide_with_bodies, is_collide_with_bodies_enabled

Property: collision_mask
Type: int
Default: 4294967295
Description: The physics layers the query will detect (as a bitmask). By default, all collision layers are detected. See Collision layers and masks in the documentation for more information.
Setget: set_collision_mask, get_collision_mask

Property: exclude
Type: Array[RID]
Default: []
Description: The list of object RIDs that will be excluded from collisions. Use CollisionObject3D.get_rid() to get the RID associated with a CollisionObject3D-derived node.
Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. To update the value you need to modify the returned array, and then assign it to the property again.
Setget: set_exclude, get_exclude

Property: margin
Type: float
Default: 0.0
Description: The collision margin for the shape.
Setget: set_margin, get_margin

Property: motion
Type: Vector3
Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0)
Description: The motion of the shape being queried for.
Setget: set_motion, get_motion

Property: shape
Type: Resource
Description: The Shape3D that will be used for collision/intersection queries. This stores the actual reference which avoids the shape to be released while being used for queries, so always prefer using this over shape_rid.
Setget: set_shape, get_shape

Property: shape_rid
Type: RID
Default: RID()
Description: The queried shape's RID that will be used for collision/intersection queries. Use this over shape if you want to optimize for performance using the Servers API.
GDScript:
var shape_rid = PhysicsServer3D.sphere_shape_create()
var radius = 2.0
PhysicsServer3D.shape_set_data(shape_rid, radius)

var params = PhysicsShapeQueryParameters3D.new()
params.shape_rid = shape_rid

# Execute physics queries here...

# Release the shape when done with physics queries.
PhysicsServer3D.free_rid(shape_rid)
C#:
RID shapeRid = PhysicsServer3D.SphereShapeCreate();
float radius = 2.0f;
PhysicsServer3D.ShapeSetData(shapeRid, radius);

var params = new PhysicsShapeQueryParameters3D();
params.ShapeRid = shapeRid;

// Execute physics queries here...

// Release the shape when done with physics queries.
PhysicsServer3D.FreeRid(shapeRid);
Setget: set_shape_rid, get_shape_rid

Property: transform
Type: Transform3D
Default: Transform3D(1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0)
Description: The queried shape's transform matrix.
Setget: set_transform, get_transform